pageContext.claim: “Twenty-five thousand people walking down the street, looters, anarchists, agitators, burning down stores, throwing things at police.”
pageContext.analysis: An absurdity. There were not 25,000 rioters marching anywhere. Think about it. The population of Sandusky, Ohio, or Helena, Mont., is about 25,000. There was not a midsize city's worth of rioters and looters throwing things at police anywhere in the country at any time.
